{{Use British English|date=June 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Isaac Hayden | image = Isaac Hayden 2013.jpg | caption = Hayden with [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in 2013 | fullname = Isaac Scot Hayden<ref>{{cite web |title = Clubs submit retained and released lists |url = http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/news/news/2013-14/jun/premier-league-clubs-submit-retained-and-released-lists.html |publisher = Premier League |date = 7 June 2013 |accessdate = 24 September 2013 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/6I4e0zuBj?url=http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/news/news/2013-14/jun/premier-league-clubs-submit-retained-and-released-lists.html |archivedate = 13 July 2013 |df = dmy-all }}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|3|22|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Chelmsford]], England | height = {{height|m=1.87}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/players/profile.html/isaac-hayden |title=Player Profile Isaac Hayden |publisher=Premier League |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140917090236/http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/players/profile.html/isaac-hayden |archivedate=17 September 2014}}</ref> | position = [[Defensive midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] | clubnumber = 14 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Brentwood Boys FC | youthyears2 = 2004–2008 | youthclubs2 = [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] | youthyears3 = 2008–2013 | youthclubs3 = [[Arsenal F.C. Academy|Arsenal]] | years1 = 2013–2016 | clubs1 = [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] | caps1 = 0 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2015–2016 | clubs2 = → [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] (loan) | caps2 = 18 | goals2 = 1 | clubs3 = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] | years3 = 2016– | caps3 = 75 | goals3 = 4 | nationalteam1 = [[England national under-16 football team|England U16]] | nationalteam2 = [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] | nationalteam3 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]] | nationalteam4 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] | nationalteam5 = [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] | nationalteam6 = [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] | nationalyears1 = 2010–2011 | nationalyears2 = 2011–2012 | nationalyears3 = 2012 | nationalyears4 = 2013–2014 | nationalyears5 = 2014–2015 | nationalyears6 = 2016 | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalcaps2 = 9 | nationalcaps3 = 1 | nationalcaps4 = 5 | nationalcaps5 = 5 | nationalcaps6 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalgoals2 = 1 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | nationalgoals4 = 0 | nationalgoals5 = 0 | nationalgoals6 = 0 | club-update = 09:11, 3 March 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 17:24, 16 November 2016 (UTC) }} '''Isaac Scot Hayden''' (born 22 March 1995) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]. Hayden has also featured for clubs [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] in his footballing career.<ref name=Profile>{{cite web|url=https://www.nufc.co.uk/teams/first-team/isaac-hayden|title=Isaac Hayden|website=NUFC.co.uk|accessdate=16 April 2017}}</ref>
==Early life== Hayden was born in [[Chelmsford]] and played for [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] until he was 13 years old.<ref name=Echo>{{cite web|url=http://www.echo-news.co.uk/sport/blues/14643472.Newcastle_new_boy_Isaac_heads_back_to_his_roots/|title=Newcastle new boy Isaac Hayden heads back to his roots|website=Echo-News.co.uk|accessdate=16 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=Academy>{{cite web|url=https://www.nufc.co.uk/news/archive/hayden-grateful-to-shrimpers|title=Hayden grateful to shrimpers|website=NUFC.co.uk|accessdate=16 April 2017}}</ref> He subsequently made the move to [[London]] to join up with that of [[Arsenal F.C. Academy|Arsenal's Academy]].<ref name=Echo /><ref name=Academy />
==Club career== ===Arsenal=== Hayden made his full debut for [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the third round of the [[Football League Cup|League Cup]] in September 2013 against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]. He started the away match playing in midfield and was substituted after 84 minutes for Swede [[Kristoffer Olsson]]. Arsenal eventually won the game on penalties at [[The Hawthorns]].<ref>{{cite news|title=West Brom 1–1 Arsenal|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24140615|accessdate=24 September 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=25 September 2014}}</ref> On 23 September 2014, Hayden made a second appearance for Arsenal, playing at centre back in another League Cup third-round game, a 1–2 home defeat against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] in September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal 1–2 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24140615|accessdate=24 September 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=23 September 2014}}</ref>
====Loan to Hull City==== On 31 July 2015, Hayden joined [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] on a season-long loan to gain first team experience.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Hayden Arrives On Loan |url=http://www.hullcitytigers.com/news/article/hayden-arrives-on-loan-2584894.aspx |publisher=Hull City AFC |date=31 July 2015 |accessdate=31 July 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150731191128/http://www.hullcitytigers.com/news/article/hayden-arrives-on-loan-2584894.aspx |archivedate=31 July 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Hayden made his debut for the club on the opening day of the 2015–16 season in a 2–0 home win to [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].<ref>{{cite news |url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33744138 |title=Hull 2–0 Huddersfield |date=8 August 2015 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref> Hayden opened his account when he scored the final goal for Hull in the 6–0 defeat of [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] on 16 January 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/35269685 |title=Hull 6–0 Charlton |date=16 January 2016 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |accessdate=16 January 2016}}</ref>
===Newcastle United=== On 11 July 2016, it was announced that Hayden has joined [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] on a five-year deal.<ref name="United Complete Hayden Signing">{{cite web | url=http://www.nufc.co.uk/articles/20160711/united-complete-hayden-signing_2281670_5720347 | title=United Complete Hayden Signing | publisher=Newcastle United F.C. | date=11 July 2016 | accessdate=11 July 2016}}</ref> Hayden scored his first goal for Newcastle in a 4–1 win over [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] on 17 August 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37030439 |title=Newcastle 4–1 Reading |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=16 August 2016 |accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref> Hayden went on to win the [[2016-17 Football League Championship|2016–17]] [[Football League Championship|Championship]] with Newcastle in May 2017.<ref name=Chronicle>{{cite web|url=http://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/newcastles-isaac-hayden-always-believed-13022364.amp|title=Newcastle's Isaac Hayden on why he always believed there'd be a Championship title-race 'twist'|website=Chronicle Live.co.uk}}</ref>
==International career== Hayden has represented England at the [[England national under-16 football team|Under 16]], [[England national under-17 football team|17]], [[England national under-18 football team|Under18]], [[England national under-19 football team|U19]], [[England national under-20 football team|U20]] and [[England national under-21 football team|Under 21]] levels of football.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/all-about/isaac-hayden|title=All about Isaac Hayden|website=Chronicle Live.co.uk|accessdate=16 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/newcastles-isaac-hayden-impresses-england-12160610.amp|title=Isaac Hayden impresses in England's U21s win|website=Chronicle Live.co.uk|accessdate=16 April 2017}}</ref>
==Style of play== [[Arsène Wenger]] has described Hayden as a player whose key assets are concentration, intelligence and strength. Equally comfortable at centre-back or in central-midfield, whilst having also previously featured at right-back and as a playmaker.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arsenal.com/news/news-archive/wenger-why-i-have-selected-hayden|title=Wenger – Why I have selected Hayden|first=Arsenal Media|last=Group|publisher=arsenal.com}}</ref>
==Personal life== Hayden is of Jamaican descent on his father’s side.{{fact|date=May 2018}}
